elements.content: Rise to Fame: Meet Jane Popular

resource.alt: woman in black and white scarf and black and white scarf photo

elements.content: Ever wonder how Jane Popular rose to astronomical fame? Let’s take a walk down memory lane.

resource.alt: Woman performing on stage with closed eyes and holding a microphone photo

elements.content: The beginning of her ascent to fame started early and young.
Her career started as a childhood singer.
By age 16, she had already sung backup vocals for 5 Grammy winning singers.

resource.alt: Woman wearing orange button collared top near red and yellow flowers

elements.content: But a sudden career pivot to the silver screen catapulted her early fame. She soon starred in 5 TV shows, and 4 major motion pictures.

resource.alt: Grayscale photo of a woman wearing white off-shoulder shirt photo

elements.content: First TV appearance with an all-star cast on the show “All Right With Us.”
Hitting her stride and making her own brand of fame.

resource.alt: Close-Up Photo of Person Wearing Brown Bonnet

elements.content: She met Quinn Darandino on the set of Kill Will, which set her movie trajectory into acceleration.

resource.alt: Woman Posing While A Person Is Operating a Camera
Monochrome Photo of Woman Sitting in Vehicle

elements.content: But a real movie star was made when she starred as Lucy Ohio in “Gone By Day.”
Her first Oscar Nomination as Best Supporting Actress in a foreign film.

resource.alt: Man Holding Camera and Woman Playing Violin

elements.content: Back to back blockbusters and Grammy nominations really made 2012 her year.
